description: Does the former cricket superstar have what it takes to lead an angry and disillusioned nation?
title: From Sportsman to Politician
title_page: From Sportsman to Politician - The New York Times
maintext:

In Sunday’s magazine, Pankaj Mishra writes about the former cricket superstar Imran Khan, who is now Pakistan’s most popular politician since Benazir Bhutto. Khan (center) with supporters at a rally in Bhakkar in April.
